#~ msgid ""
#~ "Internet Keywords make it easier for you to use well known names such as "
#~ "brand names, celebrities names, etc. For example, instead of typing "
#~ "<userinput>http://www.kde.org/</userinput>, you can just type "
#~ "<userinput>KDE</userinput>, or even <userinput>K Desktop Environment</"
#~ "userinput>. The name you type will be resolved to a <acronym>URI</"
#~ "acronym>, and you will be redirected to the appropriate location."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "KljuÄne besede za Internet vam omogoÄajo laĹžjo uporabo dobro poznanih "
#~ "imen, kot so imena blagovnih znamk, slavnostna imena, itd. Na primer "
#~ "namesto da vtipkate <emphasis>http://www.kde.org</emphasis> lahko samo "
#~ "vtipkate <emphasis>KDE</emphasis> ali celo <emphasis>K Desktop "
#~ "Environment</emphasis>. Ime, ki ga boste vtipkali, bo prevedeno v URI in "
#~ "vas bo preusmerilo na ustrezno lokacijo."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The top of the dialog has a checkbox labeled <guilabel>Enable Internet "
#~ "Keywords</guilabel>. If this option is selected, you can use Internet "
#~ "Keywords in KDE."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Vrh pogovornega okna ima potrditveno polje z oznako \"<guilabel>OmogoÄi "
#~ "kljuÄne besede za Internet</guilabel>\". Äe je ta moĹžnost izbrana, lahko "
#~ "uporabljate kljuÄne besede za internet v KDE."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Also at the top of the dialog, there is a dropdown list of all the known "
#~ "web shortcuts, which is labeled <guilabel>Fallback Search Engine</"
#~ "guilabel>. You can either select one of the shortcuts from the list or "
#~ "leave it at <guilabel>None</guilabel>. If you select a web shortcut here, "
#~ "whenever you type something that is not an Internet Keyword, your input "
#~ "will be passed to the selected web shortcut. This provides a very "
#~ "pleasant navigation and search experience, where Internet Keywords "
#~ "provide direct navigation, and you are in control of how to search for "
#~ "information when the Internet Keywords database does not contain the name "
#~ "you type. (If you select <guilabel>None</guilabel> then a directory "
#~ "listing of relevant Internet Keywords is provided instead.) Also, if you "
#~ "type something that starts with a question mark, as in <userinput>? KDE</"
#~ "userinput>, your input is directly passed to the web shortcut after "
#~ "stripping the question mark off, bypassing Internet Keywords entirely. "
#~ "This is useful when you really intend to do a search on your favorite "
#~ "search engine."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Na vrhu pogovornega okna je tudi spustni seznam vseh znanih spletnih "
#~ "bliĹžnjic, ki je oznaÄen z <guilabel>Iskalnik v primeru neuspeha</"
#~ "guilabel>. Tukaj lahko izberete eno bliĹžnjico iz seznama, ali pa pustite "
#~ "<guilabel>Nobeden</guilabel>. Äe tukaj izberete spletno bliĹžnjico, bo "
#~ "vaĹĄ vnos vsakiÄ, ko boste vtipkali nekaj kar ni kljuÄna beseda za "
#~ "Internet, podan izbrani spletni bliĹžnjici. To omogoÄa zelo prijetno "
#~ "navigiranje in isknje, kjer kljuÄne besede za Internet prinaĹĄajo "
#~ "direktno navigiranje, vi pa jih nadzorujete kako naj iĹĄÄejo informacije, "
#~ "ko podatkovna baza kljuÄnih besed za Internet ne vsebuje imena, ki ga "
#~ "vtipkate. (Äe izberete <guilabel>Nobeden</guilabel> se namesto tega "
#~ "pojavi imenik z ustreznim seznamom kljuÄnih besed za Internet.) Tudi Äe "
#~ "vtipkate nekaj kar se zaÄne z vpraĹĄajem, kot <userinput>? KDE</"
#~ "userinput>, je vaĹĄ vnos, ko se izloÄi vpraĹĄaj ven, direktno poslan k "
#~ "spletni bliĹžnjici tako, da popolnoma obidete kljuÄne besede za Internet. "
#~ "To je uporabno, ko resniÄno nameravate iskati na vaĹĄem priljubljenem "
#~ "iskalniku."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The text boxes are used not only for displaying information about an item "
#~ "in the list of web shortcuts, but also for modifying or adding new items. "
#~ "Notice that there are two buttons below the text boxes. Initially, these "
#~ "buttons have the captions <guibutton>Change</guibutton> and "
#~ "<guibutton>Delete</guibutton>, and the first of these buttons is "
#~ "disabled. Clicking the <guibutton>Delete</guibutton> button has the "
#~ "expected effect of removing the currently selected item from the list of "
#~ "web shortcuts."
